						               													<description>Rozpr&amp;aacute;vkari is a card game based on fairy tales created by Slovak writer an folclorist Pavol Dob&amp;scaron;insk&amp;yacute;. The game aims at sparking the interest in Slovak folklore and literature in younger generations by using various fairy tale references in form of a flavor text or illustrations on the playing cards. The game itself can be used as an amusing educational tool, as the scoring mechanism is supposed to make younger players practice basic mathemataical operations.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game represents the fight between good and evil. The folklore villains decided to steal all the stories in which they have lost their fight. Players try to defeat these villains and rescue the stolen fairy tales. The goal is to collect all parts of as much fairy tales as possible, using 'wish' cards and 'doucat' tokens.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game was crowdfunded in 2017.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
